Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function, and significant proteinuria with low urine specific gravity, indicating possible nephrotic syndrome or advanced kidney disease. Urine findings of brown color, cloudiness, and bilirubinuria may suggest hepatic or urinary tract involvement. No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Clinical correlation and further nephrological and hepatic evaluation are recommended.
